name: Green Graphium Butterfly Glass Necklace - Real Butterfly Jewelry
description:
A real Graphuim butterfly is set between two pieces of hand cut glass, and soldered with silver alloy and decorative beading detain. This wing is just lovely; Wonderful springy sage green markings on a deep rich black background.

The pendent is just the right size to be eye catching, but not too large, easy for everyday wear. It measures about two inches long, and an inch at the widest point. It hangs on a 16" sterling silver snake chain. The glass is encased in a silver alloy.

name: Chevron Tribal Butterfly Necklace
description:
This great southwestern inspired chevron design is created with real butterfly wings. The green and black sunset moth, the black and white idea, and the orange and black of the monarch...these are great colors and patterns.

The real wings are encased between pieces of hand cut glass, and soldered with a silver alloy. It is carefully decorated with granulation and hung on a sterling silver chain, and sterling toggle clasp. The pendant measures 1.75" x 3" and the total length is 16" (or longer on request).

The butterflies and moths I use are farmed all over the world, and collected when naturally expired. None are killed for use in my jewelry.

name: Valentine Heart Necklace with Real Sunset Moth Wings
description:
Happy Valentine's Day with this fluttering butterfly heart necklace. Real Sunset Moth wings are pressed in hand cut glass and soldered decoratively with silver alloy.

The pendant area measures about 1.75" x 1.75", and hangs on a sterling silver chain with a sterling silver toggle clasp.

The butterflies and moths I use are farmed all over the world, and collected when naturally expired. None are killed for use in my jewelry.
